DJ Patil.content:
\boxed{
\begin{enumerate}
  \item DJ Patil is an American computer scientist, music DJ, and author, born in 1990 in India.  
  \item He holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science from the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) and a Master of Science in Computer Science from the University of North Carolina at South Carolina.  
  \item Pioneered **spatial audio** technology, enabling 3D sound visualization and immersive music experiences.  
  \item Co-created the first widely used digital music player and standard for the Apple Macintosh, introducing the digital audio work (DAW) concept.  
  \item Authored the influential book *The Digital Audio Work: A Practical Guide to Creating and Using Digital Audio* (with David G. Kirk and John D. Murray).  
  \item Recognized for his contributions in the digital audio industry, including the 2018 "Best Digital Audio Engineer" award from the American Musician Association.  
  \item His work has transformed music production, and he is a leading figure in the global digital audio community.  
\end{enumerate}
}

